snippet: The National Association of Realtors said that sales increased 1.8 percent, to an annual rate of 5.53 million units last month, the highest level since February 2007.
abstract: National Assn of Realtors reports sales of existing homes rose 1.8 percent in May to annual rate of 5.53 million units, highest level since February 2007.
lead_paragraph: The National Association of Realtors said that sales increased 1.8 percent, to an annual rate of 5.53 million units last month, the highest level since February 2007.

headline.main: Existing-Home Sales Surged in May, Reaching 9-Year High
headline.print_headline: Sales of Existing Homes Surged in May
